"86:16:1" : {s: 86, a: 16, w: 1, r: "كيد", t: "وَأَكِيدُ", l: "كِيدُ", lc: 8, tl: "wa-akīdu", lb: "চক্রান্ত",e: "But I am planning", b: "আমি চাল চালি", i: "dan AKu membuat tipu daya", f: 1, rm: "To be about to, be just on the point of, be well nigh, intend, wish, practise an artful device, desire, contrive/plot/devise such a thing, worked or laboured at or upon anything, to do something clandestinely, to deceive/beguile/circumvent, means of evading/eluding, vomited, emitted fire, had menstrual flux, gave up his spirit."},
"86:16:2" : {s: 86, a: 16, w: 2, r: "كيد", t: "كَيْدًۭا", l: "كَيْد", lc: 26, tl: "kaydan", lb: "ষড়যন্ত্র, চক্রান্ত, কুট-কৌশল",e: "a plan", b: "ষড়যন্ত্র", i: "tipu daya", f: 6, rm: "To be about to, be just on the point of, be well nigh, intend, wish, practise an artful device, desire, contrive/plot/devise such a thing, worked or laboured at or upon anything, to do something clandestinely, to deceive/beguile/circumvent, means of evading/eluding, vomited, emitted fire, had menstrual flux, gave up his spirit."},
"86:17:1" : {s: 86, a: 17, w: 1, r: "مهل", t: "فَمَهِّلِ", l: "مَهِّلِ", lc: 2, tl: "famahhili", lb: "ঢিল দেওয়া, অবকাশ দেওয়া , সময় দেওয়া",e: "So give respite", b: "অবকাশ দাও", i: "maka beri tangguhlah", f: 1, rm: "To act gently or softly, act in a leisurely manner, leave one alone or grant one delay or respite."},
"86:17:2" : {s: 86, a: 17, w: 2, r: "كفر", t: "ٱلْكَٰفِرِينَ", l: "كَٰفِرُون", lc: 129, tl: "l-kāfirīna", lb: "অবিশ্বাসী, কাফির, যে ঢেকে রাখে",e: "(to) the disbelievers", b: "কাফের / অবিশ্বাসী", i: "orang-orang kafir", f: 52, rm: "to conceal, to cover, to reject, to disbelieve, to be thankless, unthankful, ungrateful, to disown, deny, faithless, black horse, dark night, tiller/farmer."},
"86:17:3" : {s: 86, a: 17, w: 3, r: "مهل", t: "أَمْهِلْهُمْ", l: "أَمْهِلْ", lc: 1, tl: "amhil'hum", lb: "অবকাশ দেওয়া",e: "Give respite to them", b: "তাদের অবকাশ দাও", i: "beritangguhlah mereka", f: 1, rm: "To act gently or softly, act in a leisurely manner, leave one alone or grant one delay or respite."},
"86:17:4" : {s: 86, a: 17, w: 4, r: "رود", t: "رُوَيْدًۢا", l: "رُوَيْد", lc: 1, tl: "ruwaydan", lb: "আস্তে আস্তে, ধীরে ধীরে",e: "little", b: "কিছুকাল", i: "sedikit/sebentar", f: 1, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.)."},
